[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 5 587 582, with reports of cases by 217 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 98.5% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with more than 1.70 million confirmed cases, now represents 30.5% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 347 872 deaths have been reported, with 343 238 (98.7%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19; Brazil is number 2 and Russia is number 3 followed by Spain at number 4. The UK is number 5, Italy is number 6, France is 7, Germany is 8, Turkey is 9, and India is number 10. China is now number 14. The USA reported the highest number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (19 790), followed by Brazil (13 051), Russia (8946), India (6414), Chile (4895), Peru (4020), Mexico (2480), the UK (2405), Saudi Arabia (2235), and Iran (2023) reporting the 10th-highest 24-hour newly confirmed case numbers. - Mod.MPP]

