[5] Germany (Frankfurt): church associated cluster
Date: Sun 24 May 2020 9:36 PM
Source: Insider, Reuters report [edited]
https://www.insider.com/germans-diagnosed-with-covid-19-after-frankfurt-church-service-2020-5


German authorities are trying to trace everyone who attended a church service in Frankfurt this month after more than 107 people tested positive for the coronavirus. Churches in the state of Hesse, where Frankfurt is located, have been able to hold services since [1 May 2020] following the easing of coronavirus lockdown restrictions, provided they adhere to official social distancing and hygiene rules.

Reuters previously reported the service took place on [10 May 2020], the city's health department deputy chief Antoni Walczok told local newspaper Frankfurter Rundschau. "This situation shows how important it is that all of us stay alert and avoid becoming careless, especially now during the easing of restrictions. The virus is still there and will spread," Hesse state health minister Kai Klose said. He said the authorities hoped that identifying those who attended the service at a Baptist church on [10 May 2020] would help prevent others being infected.

It was not immediately clear whether all the 107 with the coronavirus attended the service, or whether the tally includes people who were infected by those who did. The number of confirmed coronavirus cases in Germany has risen to 178 281, data from the Robert Koch Institute (RKI) for infectious diseases showed on Sunday [24 May 2020]. The reported death toll rose by 31 to 8247.

[Byline: Christoph Steitz; editing: Timothy Heritage]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[It seems as though religious gatherings have played a significant role in transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 -- all denominations of religion, Christian, Muslim, Jewish, Hindu. Congregating in closed quarters without uniform use of face masks and unable to meet social distancing recommendations/requirements seems to be the operative. Singing and chanting out loud further propels potentially infective droplets into the environment. A recipe for problems if someone is asymptomatic or presymptomatic and doesn't know they are a source of infection. - Mod.MPP

HealthMap/ProMED map of Germany: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7376354,3697]

